Tshidi Madia, News24Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Des van Rooyen. (Netwerk24, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories The EFF and DA are applicants in a case to have the so-called state capture report released to the public.WATCHPretoria - The Economic Freedom Fighters says Co-operative Governance Minister Des van Rooyen is a "clown" for first dropping his application to interdict the release of the Public Protector's report into "state capture", only to reapply for it.&nbsp;"He is a clown who just wants to take advantage of the court proceedings... just to procrastinate time," EFF secretary general&nbsp;Godrich Gardee told reporters ahead of court proceedings on Tuesday.&nbsp;"We are hopeful the judiciary will see the frivolity of his conduct."Gardee also took aim at President Jacob Zuma and Mineral Resources Minister Mosebenzi Zwane for their applications.&nbsp;"We know the judiciary know him [Zuma] very well, [with]... his delaying tactics." Earlier, Democratic Alliance federal council chair James Self said he was confident the matter would go their way."We've got a very,good case. The Public Protector's report is very clear," he said.The DA was a complainant in the investigation by former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela. It also made an application, along with other political parties including the EFF, to oppose the application for an interdict on the release of the report by Zuma, Van Rooyen and Zwane.&nbsp;WATCH the video:24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.